  <mainDescription>&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Purpose&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Validation Time can indicate trends in the quality and effectiveness of the test effort, the delivery process and&#xD;
    infrastructure, as well as quality of the solution itself.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Definition&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Validation Time is the combined average number of days a package spends in the qualification stages (e.g. system test,&#xD;
    integration test). This metric can be used for any aspect or phase of the verification process.&lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;br />&#xD;
    Validation Time = (average number of days a package remains in a defined validation/verification stage).&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Analysis&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    This metric is used to monitor the effort necessary to move a package through the verification cycle, regardless of&#xD;
    whether the validation is successful or not. Once a baseline duration is established, it is useful to then observe&#xD;
    whether the duration is trending upwards or downwards. Obviously, increasing validation times which can't be explained&#xD;
    by changes in test plans or specifications need investigation.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Frequency and reporting&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Validation Time should be monitored on an ongoing basis, over multiple iterations, and made available to project&#xD;
    managers, and development and validation teams.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Collection and reporting tools&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;br />&#xD;
    Validation Time can be derived from IBM&amp;reg; Rational&amp;reg; ClearQuest&amp;reg; or IBM&amp;reg; Rational&amp;reg; Team Concert&amp;reg; . The products would be&#xD;
    configured to capture the time that a package stays in one of the identified verification phases. These will have been&#xD;
    identified as part of the original deployment of the tools, and are pre-configured in most of the ClearQuest schemas&#xD;
    and RTCz process templates.&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Pitfalls, advice and countermeasures&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;br />&#xD;
    The reasons for increasing validation time need to be understood. If an unexplained increase in validation time is&#xD;
    observed, this can indicate anything from a work backlog in the validation teams, inadequate human or technical&#xD;
    resources, to issues like unanticipated increases in complexity of the solution and test procedures, or ambiguous test&#xD;
    procedures resulting in improvised or manual procedures.&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
